<subSubSection id="F39E6526C32473199488F952645FF931" box="[199,1061,1698,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BB3B36ADC32473199488F952645FF931" blockId="4.[151,1437,1338,1976]" box="[199,1061,1698,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis id="89F0EABFC32473199488F9526138F930" bold="true" box="[199,322,1698,1724]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The diagnosis is unchanged from that given by 
<bibRefCitation id="DF154B5CC32473199713F952645BF931" author="Maddison, W. P." box="[860,1057,1698,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" pagination="3" refId="ref11353" refString="Maddison, W. P. (2016) Papuaneon, a new genus of jumping spiders from Papua New Guinea (Araneae: Salticidae: Neonini). Zootaxa, 4200 (3), 437 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4200.3.9" type="journal article" year="2016">Maddison (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F39E6526C32473199488F93663D2F8C0" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BB3B36ADC32473199488F93663D2F8C0" blockId="4.[151,1437,1338,1976]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis id="89F0EABFC32473199488F9366141F96C" bold="true" box="[199,315,1734,1760]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="7C844D2EC3247319950EF93761BBF96C" authorityName="Maddison" authorityYear="2016" box="[321,449,1735,1760]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Papuaneon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="89F0EABFC3247319950EF93761BBF96C" box="[321,449,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Papuaneon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described on the basis of a male and female pair of specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="7C844D2EC3247319908EF93765E7F96C" authorityName="Maddison" authorityYear="2016" box="[1217,1437,1734,1760]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Papuaneon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tualapa">
<emphasis id="89F0EABFC3247319908EF93765E7F96C" box="[1217,1437,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Papuaneon tualapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single location in 
<collectingCountry id="C393763DC3247319958EF91B62DEF888" box="[449,676,1770,1797]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
. Further specimens of this species have now been collected from 
<collectingCountry id="C393763DC324731994D8F8FE617BF8A4" box="[151,257,1806,1832]" name="Australia" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Australia</collectingCountry>
. Examples of Australian male and female morphologies are shown in figures 3–7. There is no obvious difference between specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="C393763DC32473199664F8C262E8F8C0" box="[555,658,1842,1868]" name="Australia" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="C393763DC32473199687F8C363DEF8C0" box="[712,932,1842,1869]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F39E6526C32473199488F8A66198F834" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BB3B36ADC32473199488F8A66198F834" blockId="4.[151,1437,1338,1976]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis id="89F0EABFC32473199488F8A66185F8FC" bold="true" box="[199,511,1878,1904]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Distribution and Biology.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="643F880FC3247319960DF8A76208F8FD" box="[578,626,1879,1905]" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">type</typeStatus>
material was collected in the highlands of 
<collectingCountry id="C393763DC32473199033F8A76518F8FC" box="[1148,1378,1878,1905]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
. The Australian specimens are from high-rainfall forests in north eastern Queensland (
<figureCitation id="23BF2A28C32473199061F88A640EF819" box="[1070,1140,1914,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–7" captionStartId="5.[151,264,872,896]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,191,843]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1436,181,848]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3–7. Examples of Australian Papuaneon tualapa Maddison, 2016, female (42 002163), male (42 002167), faces (3, 4) and genitalia (5, 6). Known distribution in Australia and Papua New Guinea (7)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610164/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), as a consequence, likely IUCN Red List Category LC.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
